dation:Format=duration`\n25: \n26: **Verification**:\n27: ```bash\n28: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestCodeInterpreterSpec\n29: ```\n30: \n31: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n32: - `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct compiles without errors\n33: - `Image` field is required\n34: - `Runtime` field has enum validation and default value markers\n35: - `Timeout` field has duration format validation and default value markers\n36: - `Resources` and `Env` reference existing Sandbox types correctly\n37: - JSON tags use camelCase with `omitempty` for optional fields\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### [ ] TASK-002: Define CodeInterpreterStatus\n42: **Description**: Create `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct with ready, conditions, and observedGeneration fields.\n43: \n44: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n45: \n46: **Requirements**:\n47: - `Ready bool` - optional field, indicates whether interpreter is ready\n48: - `Conditions []metav1.Condition` - optional field, latest observations of state\n49: - `ObservedGeneration int64` - optional field, most recent generation observed by controller\n50: - Follows Kubernetes status conventions\n51: \n52: **Verification**:\n53: ```bash\n54: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestCodeInterpreterStatus\n55: ```\n56: \n57: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n58: - `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct compiles without errors\n59: - `Conditions` field uses standard Kubernetes `metav1.Condition` type\n60: - JSON tags use camelCase with `omitempty` for optional fields\n61: - Status fields are optional as per Kubernetes conventions\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### [ ] TASK-003: Define CodeInterpreter main type\n66: **Description**: Create `CodeInterpreter` struct with TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec, and Status.\n67: \n68: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n69: \n70: **Requirements**:\n71: - Embeds `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`\n72: - Contains `Spec CodeInterpreterSpec` and `Status CodeInterpreterStatus`\n73: - Kubebuilder markers:\n74:   - `+genclient`\n75:   - `+genclient:nonNamespaced` (if non-namespaced, remove if namespaced is intended)\n76:   - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object`\n77:   - `+k8s:openapi-gen=true`\n78:   - `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci;codeinterpreter`\n79:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`\n80:   - `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Ready\",type=\"boolean\",JSONPath=\".status.ready\"`\n81:   - `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Runtime\",type=\"string\",JSONPath=\".spec.runtime\"`\n82:   - `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"`\n83: \n84: **Verification**:\n85: ```bash\n86: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestCodeInterpreter\n87: ```\n88: \n89: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n90: - `CodeInterpreter` struct compiles without errors\n91: - All kubebuilder markers are present and correct\n92: - ShortNames \"ci\" and \"codeinterpreter\" are configured\n93: - Print columns for Ready, Runtime, and Age are configured\n94: - Status subresource is enabled\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### [ ] TASK-004: Define CodeInterpreterList type\n99: **Description**: Create `CodeInterpreterList` struct for collection operations.\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 761. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 Task Checklist: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Status\nStage: ST-3 (Design) - Completed\nPhase: ST-4 (Implementation) - In Progress\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Type Definition (CodeInterpreter)\n### [ ] TASK-001: Define CodeInterpreterSpec\n**Description**: Create `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct with image, runtime, timeout, resources, env, and enabledPackages fields.\n\n**Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n\n**Requirements**:\n- `Image string` - required field, container image for interpreter\n- `Runtime string` - optional field with default \"python\" and enum validation (python;javascript;typescript;go)\n- `Timeout *metav1.Duration` - optional field with default \"5m\" and duration format validation\n- `Resources *SandboxContainerResources` - optional field, reuses existing type\n- `Env []SandboxEnvVar` - optional field, reuses existing type","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/tasks-AR-002.md","time":{"start":1775840775183,"end":1775840775192}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840775209,"sessionID":"ses_287a46799ffe0U0W2ZegN3Kyn3","part":{"id":"prt_d785bc973001sw8Tc9bsomgE1U","messageID":"msg_d785bbf02001frUT5KUVwsZYGZ","sessionID":"ses_287a46799ffe0U0W2ZegN3Kyn3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c3574e3e883f4fb5812358b3caf54944","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 Delta Specification: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `CodeInterpreter` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter type metadata and API group version\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `CodeInterpreter`, and resource plural `codeinterpreters`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n14: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n15: - **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n16: - **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `CodeInterpreter`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n19: - **GIVEN** a typed client for `CodeInterpreter`\n20: - **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type\n21: - **THEN** resource name is `codeinterpreters` in plural form\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec structure with required fields\n24: \n25: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct with required fields: `Image` of type `string` for the interpreter container image, and `Runtime` of type `string` for specifying the execution environment (e.g., \"python\", \"javascript\").\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Spec requires image\n28: - **GIVEN** a new `CodeInterpreter` object being created\n29: - **WHEN** the spec is populated\n30: - **THEN** `Image` must be non-empty and contains a valid container image reference\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Runtime field specifies execution environment\n33: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with a configured runtime\n34: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to YAML\n35: - **THEN** `Runtime` contains a valid runtime identifier string\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterSpec with optional configuration fields\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterSpec` with optional fields: `Resources` of type `*SandboxContainerResources` for resource limits/requests, `Timeout` of type `*metav1.Duration` for execution timeout, `Env` of type `[]SandboxEnvVar` for environment variables, and `EnabledPackages` of type `[]string` for allowed Python/JS packages.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Optional resources field provides constraints\n42: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with resource limits defined\n43: - **WHEN** the interpreter container is created\n44: - **THEN** the container is configured with the specified CPU and memory constraints\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Timeout field limits execution duration\n47: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Timeout` set to `5m`\n48: - **WHEN** a code execution exceeds 5 minutes\n49: - **THEN** the execution is terminated with a timeout error\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Environment variables are injected\n52: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with environment variables defined\n53: - **WHEN** the interpreter container starts\n54: - **THEN** the specified environment variables are available in the execution context\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Package filtering restricts available libraries\n57: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `EnabledPackages` set to `[\"numpy\", \"pandas\"]`\n58: - **WHEN** code attempts to import `tensorflow`\n59: - **THEN** the import is blocked and an error is returned\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterStatus with conditions support\n62: \n63: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct with optional `Conditions` field of type `[]metav1.Condition` for tracking interpreter state transitions, and `Ready` field of type `bool` to indicate if the interpreter is ready to execute code.\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Status conditions are optional\n66: - **GIVEN** a newly created `CodeInterpreter` resource\n67: - **WHEN** status is initially empty\n68: - **THEN** resource creation succeeds without requiring conditions\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Ready field reflects operational state\n71: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `CodeInterpreter` lifecycle\n72: - **WHEN** the interpreter container becomes ready\n73: - **THEN** `Ready` is set to `true` in the status\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Condition updates follow Kubernetes conventions\n76: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `CodeInterpreter` lifecycle\n77: - **WHEN** transitioning between states (e.g., Provisioning → Ready)\n78: - **THEN** conditions are added with appropriate types, reasons, and transition timestamps\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreterList type for collection operations\n81: \n82: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterList` as a standard Kubernetes list type containing `[]CodeInterpreter` items and standard list metadata.\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: List type supports pagination\n85: - **GIVEN** multiple `CodeInterpreter` resources in a namespace\n86: - **WHEN** `List` operation is called with `ListOptions.Limit`\n87: - **THEN** response returns a `CodeInterpreterList` with `Continue` token when more items exist\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: Scheme registration for serialization\n90: \n91: The system SHALL register `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types in the Kubernetes scheme for proper JSON/YAML serialization and deserialization.\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: YAML deserialization produces correct Go types\n94: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: CodeInterpreter` in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n95: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded using the registered scheme\n96: - **THEN** a `CodeInterpreter` struct instance is created with correct field mappings\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: List kind maps to CodeInterpreterList\n99: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: CodeInterpreterList`\n100: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded\n101: - **THEN** a `CodeInterpreterList` struct instance is created with items as `[]CodeInterpreter`\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: CRD subresources support\n104: \n105: The system SHALL enable status subresource on `CodeInterpreter` to allow independent updates to status without modifying spec.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Status update does not modify spec\n108: - **GIVEN** an existing `CodeInterpreter` with both spec and status\n109: - **WHEN** a status-only update is performed via API server\n110: - **THEN** only status fields change and spec remains unmodified\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Status and spec have independent versioning\n113: - **GIVEN** a controller updating status\n114: - **WHEN** status changes multiple times\n115: - **THEN** each status update increments `metadata.generation` independently of spec modifications\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: Default values for spec fields\n118: \n119: The system SHALL define kubebuilder markers to set default values: `Timeout` defaults to `\"5m\"` and `Runtime` defaults to `\"python\"`.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Missing timeout field receives default\n122: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` created without explicit timeout value\n123: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n124: - **THEN** `Timeout` is set to `5m` automatically\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Missing runtime field receives default\n127: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` created without explicit runtime value\n128: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n129: - **THEN** `Runtime` is set to `\"python\"` automatically\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Explicit values override defaults\n132: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` created with custom timeout and runtime values\n133: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n134: - **THEN** the explicit values are preserved and defaults are not applied\n135: \n136: ### Requirement: OpenAPI validation for spec fields\n137: \n138: The system SHALL generate OpenAPI v3 schema for `CodeInterpreter` to enable validation of field types, required fields, and constraints.\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Required field validation\n141: - **GIVEN** a request creating `CodeInterpreter` without required `Image`\n142: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n143: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating `image` is required\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Runtime field validates against allowed values\n146: - **GIVEN** a request creating `CodeInterpreter` with invalid runtime value\n147: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n148: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid runtime value\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Timeout field validates duration format\n151: - **GIVEN** a request creating `CodeInterpreter` with invalid duration format\n152: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n153: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid duration format\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: Print columns for kubectl readability\n156: \n157: The system SHALL configure additional printer columns for `kubectl get` output, including `Ready` derived from `status.ready`, `Runtime` derived from `spec.runtime`, and `Age` derived from `metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Ready column displays correctly\n160: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` resource with `Ready` set to `true`\n161: - **WHEN** `kubectl get codeinterpreters` is executed\n162: - **THEN** the Ready column shows `True`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Runtime column displays configured runtime\n165: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` resource with `Runtime` set to `\"python\"`\n166: - **WHEN** `kubectl get codeinterpreters` is executed\n167: - **THEN** the Runtime column shows `python`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Age column displays correctly\n170: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` resource that was created 10 minutes ago\n171: - **WHEN** `kubectl get codeinterpreters` is executed\n172: - **THEN** the Age column shows `10m` or equivalent time duration\n173: \n174: ### Requirement: CRD status storage optimization\n175: \n176: The system SHALL use status subresource to ensure status updates are stored efficiently and do not trigger spec reconciliation unnecessarily.\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Frequent status updates\n179: - **GIVEN** a controller updating `CodeInterpreter` status every 30 seconds\n180: - **WHEN** multiple status updates occur\n181: - **THEN** each update only writes to status subresource and does not trigger full reconciliation\n182: \n183: ### Requirement: Type registration in code-generation\n184: \n185: The system SHALL ensure `CodeInterpreter` types are included in the client-go code-generation pipeline to produce typed clients, informers, and listers.\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Typed client operations work\n188: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance from generated client-go code\n189: - **WHEN** calling `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create`\n190: - **THEN** the operation succeeds with proper type safety and returns a `CodeInterpreter` pointer\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Informer factory recognizes CodeInterpreter\n193: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` for the runtime API group\n194: - **WHEN** `Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` is called\n195: - **THEN** an informer watching `codeinterpreters` resources is returned\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: JSON tag naming convention\n198: \n199: The system SHALL use camelCase JSON tags for all fields to match Kubernetes API conventions and client-go expectations.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: JSON serialization uses camelCase\n202: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` struct populated with Go fields\n203: - **WHEN** serialized to JSON\n204: - **THEN** the JSON keys are camelCase (e.g., `image`, `runtime`, `timeout`, `resources`)\n205: \n206: ### Requirement: DeepCopy methods for safety\n207: \n208: The system SHALL implement `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `CodeInterpreter` to support safe copying in controllers.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: DeepCopy creates independent instance\n211: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` instance with populated fields\n212: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy` is called\n213: - **THEN** the returned copy is independent and modifications to the copy do not affect the original\n214: \n215: ### Requirement: Validation markers for fields\n216: \n217: The system SHALL use kubebuilder validation markers to enforce constraints on spec fields where applicable.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Image field validates format\n220: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Image` set to invalid format\n221: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n222: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating invalid image format\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Timeout field validates minimum duration\n225: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Timeout` set to `\"1s\"`\n226: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n227: - **THEN** validation passes as the timeout is at minimum allowed duration\n228: \n229: ### Requirement: Label selector support for listing\n230: \n231: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes label selectors when listing `CodeInterpreter` resources.\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Label selector filters results\n234: - **GIVEN** multiple `CodeInterpreter` resources with different labels\n235: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector matching a specific label\n236: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are returned\n237: \n238: ### Requirement: Watch support for controller integration\n239: \n240: The system SHALL support watch operations on `CodeInterpreter` resources to enable controllers to react to changes efficiently.\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: Watch events notify of changes\n243: - **GIVEN** a watch stream established on `CodeInterpreter` resources\n244: - **WHEN** a new `CodeInterpreter` is created\n245: - **THEN** the watch stream receives an ADDED event with the new resource\n246: \n247: ### Requirement: Runtime validation for supported languages\n248: \n249: The system SHALL validate that the `Runtime` field contains one of the supported execution environments: `\"python\"`, `\"javascript\"`, `\"typescript\"`, or `\"go\"`.\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Valid runtime values are accepted\n252: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Runtime` set to `\"python\"`\n253: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n254: - **THEN** creation succeeds without validation errors\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Invalid runtime values are rejected\n257: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `Runtime` set to `\"ruby\"`\n258: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n259: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating unsupported runtime\n260: \n261: ### Requirement: Package validation for security\n262: \n263: The system SHALL validate that packages listed in `EnabledPackages` follow naming conventions and do not contain malicious patterns.\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Valid package names are accepted\n266: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `EnabledPackages` set to `[\"numpy\", \"pandas\"]`\n267: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n268: - **THEN** creation succeeds without validation errors\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: Invalid package names are rejected\n271: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with `EnabledPackages` set to `[\"../../../etc/passwd\"]`\n272: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n273: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid package name\n274: \n275: ### Requirement: Namespace-scoped resource\n276: \n277: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a namespace-scoped resource (not cluster-scoped) to allow multiple interpreters per namespace.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Resource exists in namespace scope\n280: - **GIVEN** two namespaces `dev` and `prod`\n281: - **WHEN** creating a `CodeInterpreter` named `main` in each namespace\n282: - **THEN** both resources can exist independently with the same name\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: List operations respect namespace\n285: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreter` resources in multiple namespaces\n286: - **WHEN** `List` is called without namespace specified\n287: - **THEN** only resources in the configured namespace are returned\n288: \n289: ### Requirement: Finalizers for cleanup\n290: \n291: The system SHALL support finalizers on `CodeInterpreter` to ensure proper cleanup of associated resources (pods, PVCs, etc.) before deletion.\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Finalizer prevents immediate deletion\n294: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` with active pods and a finalizer\n295: - **WHEN** a delete request is issued\n296: - **THEN** the resource is marked for deletion but not removed until the finalizer is removed\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: Finalizer enables graceful cleanup\n299: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `CodeInterpreter` resources\n300: - **WHEN** deletion is detected and cleanup is complete\n301: - **THEN** the controller removes the finalizer and the resource is garbage collected\n\n(End of file - total 301 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 Delta Specification: CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `CodeInterpreter` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter type metadata and API group version\n\nThe system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `CodeInterpreter`, and resource plural `codeinterpreters`.\n\n#### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n- **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n- **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `CodeInterpreter`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n- **GIVEN** a typed client for `CodeInterpreter`\n- **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775840775181,"end":1775840775206}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840775214,"sessionID":"ses_287a46799ffe0U0W2ZegN3Kyn3","part":{"id":"prt_d785bc6f2001xspqk53g0CzrCx","messageID":"msg_d785bbf02001frUT5KUVwsZYGZ","sessionID":"ses_287a46799ffe0U0W2ZegN3Kyn3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6a91337c2b974403b4642dcdb8fe6b89","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-002/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CodeInterpreter CRD Type Definition Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/apis`  \n6: **Language**: Go  \n7: **Size**: S  \n8: **Purpose**: Define Kubernetes CRD type definitions for CodeInterpreter resources, enable client-go code generation, and provide type-safe API access for code execution environment management.\n9: \n10: ## Architecture\n11: \n12: ### Package Structure\n13: \n14: ```\n15: pkg/apis/\n16: └── runtime/\n17:     └── v1alpha1/\n18:         ├── types.go                   # Core type definitions (AgentRuntime + Sandbox types)\n19:         ├── register.go                # Scheme registration\n20:         ├── doc.go                     # Package documentation\n21:         ├── deepcopy.go                # DeepCopy methods (generated)\n22:         └── types_test.go              # Unit tests\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### API Group\n26: \n27: - **Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n28: - **Version**: `v1alpha1`\n29: - **Scope**: `Namespaced`\n30: - **Kind**: `CodeInterpreter`\n31: - **Resource Plural**: `codeinterpreters`\n32: - **Short Names**: `ci`\n33: \n34: ### Component Interactions\n35: \n36: ```\n37: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n38: │                     Kubernetes API Server                   │\n39: │                                                             │\n40: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n41: │  │       runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1          │  │\n42: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n43: │  │  │  codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh │  │  │\n44: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n45: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n46: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n47:                            │\n48:                            │ k8s client-go\n49:                            ▼\n50: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n51: │                  client-go (Generated)                     │\n52: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n53: │  │  clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/         │  │\n54: │  │    • CodeInterpreterInterface                        │  │\n55: │  │    • REST CRUD + Watch                               │  │\n56: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n57: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n58: │  │  informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/        │  │\n59: │  │    • CodeInterpreterInformer                         │  │\n60: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n61: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n62: │  │  listers/runtime/v1alpha1/                          │  │\n63: │  │    • CodeInterpreterLister                           │  │\n64: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n65: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n66:                            │\n67:                            │ Controllers\n68:                            ▼\n69: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n70: │                   Code Execution Components                 │\n71: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐ │\n72: │  │  PicoD Daemon   │  │  Session Store  │  │  Router     │ │\n73: │  │  (per pod)      │  │  (Redis)        │  │  (Nginx)    │ │\n74: │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────┘ │\n75: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ## Data Structures\n79: \n80: ### CodeInterpreter\n81: \n82: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: // +genclient\n86: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n87: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n88: // +kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci;codeinterpreter\n89: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n90: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Ready\",type=\"boolean\",JSONPath=\".status.ready\"\n91: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Runtime\",type=\"string\",JSONPath=\".spec.runtime\"\n92: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n93: \n94: // CodeInterpreter defines a custom resource for managing code execution environments.\n95: // It represents a code interpreter sandbox that executes user code in a secure environment.\n96: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n97:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n98:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n99: \n100:     Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n101:     Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n102: }\n103: \n104: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of a CodeInterpreter.\n105: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n106:     // Image is the container image for the interpreter (e.g., \"python:3.11-slim\").\n107:     // +required\n108:     Image string `json:\"image\"`\n109: \n110:     // Runtime specifies the execution environment type.\n111:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"python\"\n112:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=python;javascript;typescript;go\n113:     // +optional\n114:     Runtime string `json:\"runtime,omitempty\"`\n115: \n116:     // Timeout defines the maximum execution time for code snippets.\n117:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"5m\"\n118:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n119:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Format=duration\n120:     // +optional\n121:     Timeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n122: \n123:     // Resources defines compute resource requirements for the interpreter container.\n124:     // +optional\n125:     Resources *SandboxContainerResources `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n126: \n127:     // Env defines environment variables to inject into the interpreter container.\n128:     // +optional\n129:     Env []SandboxEnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n130: \n131:     // EnabledPackages specifies allowed packages for the interpreter.\n132:     // Only packages listed here can be imported/required. Empty list allows all.\n133:     // +optional\n134:     EnabledPackages []string `json:\"enabledPackages,omitempty\"`\n135: }\n136: \n137: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of a CodeInterpreter.\n138: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n139:     // Ready indicates whether the interpreter is ready to execute code.\n140:     // +optional\n141:     Ready bool `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n142: \n143:     // Conditions represent the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's current state.\n144:     // +optional\n145:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n146: \n147:     // ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed by the controller.\n148:     // +optional\n149:     ObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n150: }\n151: \n152: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n153: \n154: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter objects.\n155: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n156:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n157:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n158: \n159:     Items []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### SandboxContainerResources (Reused from AgentRuntime)\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: // SandboxContainerResources defines resource requirements for a container.\n167: type SandboxContainerResources struct {\n168:     // Limits defines the resource limits.\n169:     // +optional\n170:     Limits SandboxResourceList `json:\"limits,omitempty\"`\n171: \n172:     // Requests defines the resource requests.\n173:     // +optional\n174:     Requests SandboxResourceList `json:\"requests,omitempty\"`\n175: }\n176: \n177: // SandboxResourceList defines a list of resources.\n178: type SandboxResourceList struct {\n179:     // CPU defines CPU resources.\n180:     // +optional\n181:     CPU string `json:\"cpu,omitempty\"`\n182: \n183:     // Memory defines memory resources.\n184:     // +optional\n185:     Memory string `json:\"memory,omitempty\"`\n186: \n187:     // EphemeralStorage defines ephemeral storage resources.\n188:     // +optional\n189:     EphemeralStorage string `json:\"ephemeralStorage,omitempty\"`\n190: }\n191: ```\n192: \n193: ### SandboxEnvVar (Reused from AgentRuntime)\n194: \n195: ```go\n196: // SandboxEnvVar defines an environment variable.\n197: type SandboxEnvVar struct {\n198:     // Name is the name of the environment variable.\n199:     // +required\n200:     Name string `json:\"name\"`\n201: \n202:     // Value is the literal value of the environment variable.\n203:     // +optional\n204:     Value string `json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n205: \n206:     // ValueFrom specifies a source for the value.\n207:     // +optional\n208:     ValueFrom *SandboxEnvVarSource `json:\"valueFrom,omitempty\"`\n209: }\n210: \n211: // SandboxEnvVarSource defines a source for environment variable values.\n212: type SandboxEnvVarSource struct {\n213:     // FieldRef selects a field from the pod.\n214:     // +optional\n215:     FieldRef *SandboxFieldRef `json:\"fieldRef,omitempty\"`\n216: \n217:     // ConfigMapKeyRef selects a key from a ConfigMap.\n218:     // +optional\n219:     ConfigMapKeyRef *SandboxConfigMapKeyRef `json:\"configMapKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n220: \n221:     // SecretKeyRef selects a key from a Secret.\n222:     // +optional\n223:     SecretKeyRef *SandboxSecretKeyRef `json:\"secretKeyRef,omitempty\"`\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### Scheme Registration\n228: \n229: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n230: \n231: ```go\n232: package v1alpha1\n233: \n234: import (\n235:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n236:     k8sruntime \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n237:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n238:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/serializer\"\n239:     k8sutil \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime\"\n240: )\n241: \n242: var (\n243:     SchemeBuilder = k8sruntime.NewSchemeBuilder(addKnownTypes)\n244:     AddToScheme   = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n245: )\n246: \n247: // SchemeGroupVersion is group version used to register these objects.\n248: var SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n249: \n250: // Resource takes an unqualified resource and returns a Group qualified GroupResource.\n251: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource {\n252:     return SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(resource).GroupResource()\n253: }\n254: \n255: var (\n256:     // Scheme is the runtime.Scheme for the API types.\n257:     Scheme = k8sruntime.NewScheme()\n258: \n259:     // Codecs provides methods for retrieving codecs and serializers for the scheme.\n260:     Codecs = serializer.NewCodecFactory(Scheme)\n261: \n262:     // ParameterCodec handles versioning of objects that are converted to query parameters.\n263:     ParameterCodec = k8sruntime.NewParameterCodec(Scheme)\n264: )\n265: \n266: func init() {\n267:     // Add the Kubernetes types to the scheme.\n268:     metav1.AddToGroupVersion(Scheme, schema.GroupVersion{Version: \"v1\"})\n269:     k8sutil.Must(AddToScheme(Scheme))\n270: }\n271: \n272: // addKnownTypes adds the set of known types to the supplied scheme.\n273: func addKnownTypes(scheme *k8sruntime.Scheme) error {\n274:     scheme.AddKnownTypes(SchemeGroupVersion,\n275:         &AgentRuntime{},\n276:         &AgentRuntimeList{},\n277:         &CodeInterpreter{},\n278:         &CodeInterpreterList{},\n279:     )\n280:     metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n281:     return nil\n282: }\n283: ```\n284: \n285: **File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go`\n286: \n287: ```go\n288: // Package v1alpha1 contains API Schema definitions for the runtime v1alpha1 API group.\n289: //\n290: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen=package\n291: // +k8s:conversion-gen=github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis\n292: // +k8s:openapi-gen=true\n293: // +k8s:defaulter-gen=TypeMeta\n294: // +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n295: package v1alpha1\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ## API Contracts\n299: \n300: ### CRD Manifest\n301: \n302: **CodeInterpreter CRD** (generated by `controller-gen`)\n303: \n304: ```yaml\n305: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n306: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n307: metadata:\n308:   annotations:\n309:     controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2\n310:   name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n311: spec:\n312:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n313:   names:\n314:     kind: CodeInterpreter\n315:     listKind: CodeInterpreterList\n316:     plural: codeinterpreters\n317:     shortNames:\n318:     - ci\n319:     singular: codeinterpreter\n320:   scope: Namespaced\n321:   versions:\n322:   - name: v1alpha1\n323:     schema:\n324:       openAPIV3Schema:\n325:         description: CodeInterpreter defines a custom resource for managing code execution environments.\n326:         properties:\n327:           apiVersion:\n328:             description: 'APIVersion defines the versioned schema of this representation\n329:               of an object.'\n330:             type: string\n331:           kind:\n332:         